      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that the mathematical model form (constitutive law, contact formulation, geometry representation) is appropriate for the COU physics.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening constitutive model applied to titanium alloy consistent with published material characterization data. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) applied at screw-rod interface based on literature values. Geometric nonlinearity enabled to capture large-displacement response at 40 mm displacement target."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
