      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry, and boundary conditions traceable to measured data or published standards with uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy material properties (E=114 GPa, yield=880 MPa) sourced from coupon tensile testing of production material. Geometry derived from CAD files of production screw and rod. Uncertainty in material inputs propagated through model; sensitivity analysis confirms QoI is most sensitive to yield strength (±5% effect on yield force)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
