      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of COU loading conditions or justify single-condition testing with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 loading configuration (compression-bending, 10° offset). Multiple loading angles not evaluated due to resource constraints. Sensitivity analysis indicates stiffness QoI is relatively insensitive to angle variation (±2° produces <4% change), partially mitigating this gap. Factor achievedLevel below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs must be shown equivalent to the experimental test inputs within quantified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Measured specimen dimensions compared to nominal CAD dimensions; all within ±0.05 mm manufacturing tolerance. Applied load and displacement measured by calibrated load cell and LVDT. Boundary conditions in FEA replicate fixture geometry within 0.1 mm. Equivalency confirmed for all primary input parameters."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of FEA outputs to experimental measurements using pre-established acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96 and QoI difference < 10%).",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: FEA 312 N/mm vs. experimental mean 308 N/mm (1.3% difference, E/uval=0.42). Yield force: FEA 1,847 N vs. experimental mean 1,823 N (1.3% difference, E/uval=0.61). Force at 40 mm: FEA 2,104 N vs. experimental mean 2,089 N (0.7% difference, E/uval=0.33). All acceptance criteria met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
